Pray for Türkiye & Syria…

My heart is grieving with everyone who has lost loved ones, homes, and livelihoods both there and in Syria.

#prayforturkiye #prayforsyria

Texas is where it all started for me… Stepping foot back onto a stage there flooded my memories…. Full of family, friends, and fellow musicians that pushed me to pursue a lofty dream that I didn’t realize would take a decade+ of hard work and ambition to pursue…. It never looked like I imagined… That sheltered little Texas-born, Egyptian-American girl that spent hours alone in her room, writing in her butterfly journal, trying to figure out how to use her voice, and dreaming of seeing the world, got to see more than she ever thought possible. I’ve also experienced many losses and rejections I didn’t expect and hurdles that I am still trying to climb over… I would do it all over again for those irreplaceable friendships and experiences. <— That’s why I choose to keep going, because being able to connect with so many through lyric and musical interpretation of the trials we face alone, give myself, and that little girl in me, a purposeful and joyful life.

Thank you for living this dream with me. It wouldn’t exist without you. 

📸: @clamsjog

A painting I did years ago called “the gift of the scarab”… In ancient Egyptian history, it symbolizes renewal, the sun’s death and rebirth every morning on the horizon, and protection in the afterlife. After I buried my father in Egypt, I kept seeing these iridescent creatures and it gave me a sense of hope for the future… of healing… 

My city feels so heavy after the recent tragedies… We are in desperate need of change… renewal… protection. My heart is with the families who are forever mourning their children. 

I will never have the right words, but it doesn’t feel right to not say anything at all. I wish we could undo the devastation of our past, but I know we can do all in our power to change our days ahead... I can see the sun on the horizon.

We all have the right to our opinions, the right to vote, and to make the right changes to protect one another, especially our children. 

#commonsensegunlaws

Carne Con Chile Rojo Tacos! Recipe below…

Did you know that I also work as a personal chef in Nashville when I am not making music and performing? I have a passion for custom cakes and pastries, but I also work for a service called, @castironkitchen! Here’s one of my favorite recipes to make…

Braised Beef: 
2lbs beef chuck roast 
3/4 cup maple syrup 
1/4 cup olive oil
4 cups beef or vegetable broth 
10 guajillo + New Mexico chiles (whole,mild)
1 yellow onion, quartered
1 T peppercorns
1 T kosher salt 
2  tomatoes, sliced 
4 sage stems 

Red Chile Sauce: 
12 guajillo + New Mexico chiles 
4-6 chiles de arbol 
2 T olive oil
1/2 medium onion 
4 cloves of garlic 
2 t kosher salt 
2 cups of braising liquid

Sprinkle some salt and raw sugar over the beef on each side. Sear over high heat for 5-7minutes until browned. Place in pot with other braising ingredients and braise for 3-4hrs at 275F (until tender). Stem and clean chiles well, removing seeds. Bring water to a boil and soak the chiles for about 10 min. Place all sauce ingredients in a blender until smooth. Simmer meat in red chile sauce for another 30 minutes. Serve over fresh corn or flour tortillas with pico de gallo, cotija cheese, avocado crema, and lime!

“How do you move when everything scares you? 
One step at a time. 
How can you sing when your own thoughts abuse you?
One word at a time. 
How does your heart keep on beating? 
One breath at a time.”

On the days you feel like an imposter… I hope you see how much you’ve grown and not distracted by thoughts of inadequacy… If you are growing, you are alive! If we are actively, gratefully present with who we’ve become and not regretfully looking at our past or anticipating becoming a different version of ourselves… We might actually enjoy the process of LIVING… I am working on that every day. 

📸: @clamsjog

Hi, I am Deena and I started Biscuits & Baklava earlier this year out of a passion for custom designed cakes and a love for creating an array of delicious goodies from French macarons, pies and pastries, to baklava and other middle eastern treats. My mom gifted me with the name “Biscuits & Bakalva,” originally meant to be the title of her unwritten book about marrying into Egyptian culture, but is now living as the name of my little bakery, inspired by the blend of my American and Egyptian heritage… I learned so much from my grandmothers on both sides, who sparked a passion in me for cooking and baking… From tea cakes and pies to baklava and kunafa… Creating memorable moments around the table is something that brings me great joy and I am so happy to share this with you! 🥧

Shoot me a DM- Let’s talk about how we can elevate your next gathering!

Happy Hallow’s Eve! Let’s talk pie! I am taking orders for Thanksgiving week with some twists on the classic flavors, and decorative pie art to level up your already beautiful holiday table display. Swipe to see some examples! I had the honor of making these two pie babies for @malloryervin’s birthday last week. 🥧

Available Flavors: 

- Pumpkin Cheesecake Pie with Gingersnap Crust
* A touch of orange zest to compliment the decadent spices and decorative maple whipped cream topping! 

- Brown Sugar Apple Pie with Fig Jam Glaze 
* This open faced pie has a rosette of apple slices covering the flaky crust. The fig jam glaze balances out the tartness of Granny Smith and Honey Crisp apples. 

- Bourbon Caramel Pecan Pie with Sea Salt
* Ok, pecan pie is one of my favorites that my mom and grandma would make, but I am adding a silky creaminess to that traditional crunch with a slight boozy finish and topped with extra caramel sauce and flaky sea salt. 

- Dark Cherry & Chocolate Urfa Pie
* The subtle kick of this smoky, tart Turkish chili called “Urfa Biber” compliments the dark cherries and is smoothed out by the richness of melted dark chocolate and a buttery crust! Try the pie! 🤗

*Decoration will vary.
*Delivery available (Nashville and surrounding areas)!

Meet the incredible Deena Jakoub, the powerhouse behind music that moves us, and the reason we felt a need to take the MMP team to Tennessee to explore the healing power of music. Set in Nashville's vibrant scene with a heart that beats for her Egyptian heritage, Deena's journey is one of passion and resilience. In our interview, she shares the profound impact of music on healing through loss of a loved one and the beautiful community it has built. Be sure to check it out if you missed it! 

Her creativity extends beyond music though - she’s started a new pastry business - “Biscuits and Baklava” with custom cakes, cookies, and Middle Eastern inspired desserts. 

This amazing, multitalented woman continues to inspire us, and we are so grateful to have had the opportunity to meet with her!
